Sentencas: Thermal, electrical, and electrocatalytical properties of the oxygen deficient La0.5Sr0.2TiO2.95 perovskite are studied in relation to their possible use as solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode material.
Titulo: La0.5Sr0.2TiO3-δ Perovskite as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: La(0.5)Sr(0.2)TiO(2.9)5 is chemically stable under air and reduced atmosphere.
Titulo: La0.5Sr0.2TiO3-δ Perovskite as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Its thermal expansion coefficient is close to that of yttrium-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) under air and Ar/H-2 (5%).
Titulo: La0.5Sr0.2TiO3-δ Perovskite as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: No significant chemical expansion or contraction of La0.5Sr0.2TiO2.95 are observed between air and reduced atmosphere.
Titulo: La0.5Sr0.2TiO3-δ Perovskite as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: La0.5Sr0.2TiO2.95 material has an electrical conductivity at 800 degrees C of 1S cm(-1) under moist hydrogen (H-2/H2O (3%)), reaching 10 S cm(-1) when LSTO is prereduced under Ar/H-2(5%).
Titulo: La0.5Sr0.2TiO3-δ Perovskite as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of La0.5Sr0.2TiO2.95 at 800 degrees C under moist hydrogen is about 1.5 Omega cm(2), a value which has been obtained when including a thin CGO buffer layer between the dense YSZ electrolyte and the porous electrode.
Titulo: La0.5Sr0.2TiO3-δ Perovskite as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
